Central African president returns home amid mutiny . Central African Republic President Ange - Felix Patasse returned home on Monday despite a pledge by army mutineers to oust him , loyalist sources said . They said Patasse , who was in Europe when the revolt started on November 16 , flew home after a stopover in Gabon . French troops based in the capital Bangui have been patrolling the city and control access to the airport , making it impossible to check on the atmosphere at the president ' s arrival . Rebel soldiers on Monday demanded Patasse ' s dismissal , saying he should not return from an official visit to France . 
